dspace-development.title: Restore and test a database backup for the DataSpace installation

comments.body: Currently the postgresql backups are written exclusively within the production environment, within the directory `/home/dspace/dspace/backup`. These should be rsync'd to the staging environment.

The following retrieves title metadata values for any given Item within the database:

```sql
select i.item_id,v.text_value, r.element, r.qualifier from item as i inner join metadatavalue as v on v.resource_id=i.item_id inner join metadatafieldregistry as r on v.metadata_field_id=r.metadata_field_id where r.element = 'title';
```

The following retrieves the theses submission Items imported for the 2020 graduating class:

```sql
select i.item_id,v.text_value, r.element, r.qualifier from item as i inner join metadatavalue as v on v.resource_id=i.item_id inner join metadatafieldregistry as r on v.metadata_field_id=r.metadata_field_id where r.element = 'date' and r.qualifier='classyear' and v.text_value='2020';
```

orangelight.title: ETAS links should not show if an item is charged

comments.body: Here is an example of a checked out item, that is not hiding the link. https://catalog-staging.princeton.edu/catalog/611143

When the item still displayed the link it was marked as "On Hold" in the availability lookup. Once it transitioned to "Charged" the link went away. I wonder if this a upper/lower case issue since the javascript is looking for "On hold" and the availability status from bibdata had "Hold" capitalized.
Thanks for figuring that out @kevinreiss; made it very easy to put up a fix.
